The paper introduces a model that learns active learning algorithms via metalearning, which involves learning a data representation, an item selection heuristic, and a method for constructing prediction functions from labeled training sets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses the Omniglot and MovieLens datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research, respectively. Finally, the paper's focus on active learning and item selection suggests that it may also be relevant to the Software Engineering (cs.SD) sub-category, which includes research on software development processes and tools.
